Class ModifyPart

  • java.lang.Object
    • ModifyPart
  • public class ModifyPart
extends java.lang.Object
    Controls the 'Modify Part' interface Using a Part as reference to populate the proper fields the user can generate a new Part object.

      • close_window

        public void close_window​(javafx.stage.Stage stage)
        Takes Stage instance as arg This function takes a stage instance as argument and calls its close() function. This fixed an issue with calling Close_program from within BeginStart() as a Stage instance with a value of null would be called instead. Close_program implements "close_program.fxml" to confirm the user's action. If the user applies their changes the function save_button_listener() is called.
        Parameters:
        stage - Stage

      • change_detect

        public boolean change_detect​(Part part)
        Takes Part arg Returns boolean. This function determines if the user has made any modifications, allowing the program to close without prompting confirmation if no changes were detected.
        Parameters:
        part - Part
        Returns:
        boolean
